instruction:
A method has a return type, a name, parameters, and a body:

```java
static returnType methodName(paramType param) {
    return value;
}
```

`void` means it returns nothing. `static` means you can call it from `main` without creating an object.

Run this — then notice how `greet` is called twice with different names.

starter:
public class Main {
    static String greet(String name) {
        return "Hello, " + name + "!";
    }

    static void printSeparator() {
        System.out.println("----------");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(greet("Alice"));
        System.out.println(greet("Bob"));
        printSeparator();
        System.out.println(greet("Carol"));
    }
}

